Though Columbia consistently performed below the top quartile in 10-year Rolling Performance,

Columbia’s endowment has the lowest risk percentage compared to other top institutions.

MIT has the single highest 10 year annualized return percentage at 13.02 in 2022. Columbia had a return percentage of 8.77%. MIT also has an endowment with the highest risk percentage at 22.4% Columbia has almost half the risk of MIT at 11.6%. Columbia’s endowment has a much lower risk compared to all other top institutions. All top institutions outperformed the 70-30 Global index fund.
